ymbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:1903409 ! reactive oxygen species biosynthetic process\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25714\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-07-12T14:21:06Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141105\nname: obsolete suppression of host toll-like receptor signal transduction\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process in which a symbiont interferes with, inhibits or disrupts a toll-like receptor signaling pathway in the host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:15944308, PMID:17299722, PMID:18327267]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents the same process as symbiont-mediated suppression of host toll-like receptor signal transduction ; GO:0039722.\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated disruption of host toll-like receptor signaling pathway\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated suppression of host toll-like receptor signal transduction\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated suppression of host toll-like receptor signaling pathway\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26183\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26686\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0039722\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-09-27T14:37:00Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141114\nname: obsolete symbiont-mediated suppression of host complement activation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process by which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal execution of the activation of complement in its host.\" [PMID:20194595, PMID:25830295]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents the same process as GO:0042784.\nsynonym: \"suppression of complement activation by another organism\" BROAD []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26389\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0042784\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-11-22T15:22:34Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141115\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host complement activation by inactivation of complement proteins\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process by which a symbiont disrupts or prematurely activates host complement so that its microbial-destroying activities fail.\" [PMID:24312361, PMID:34305859]\nsynonym: \"suppression of complement activation by another organism by inactivation of complement proteins\" BROAD []\nis_a: GO:0042784 ! symbiont-mediated suppression of host complement activation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26389\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-11-22T15:32:58Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141116\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host complement activation by complement sequestering\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process by which a symbiont prevents host complement activation by sequestering it away from its surface.\" [PMID:18323455]\nsynonym: \"suppression of complement activation by another organism by complement sequestering\" BROAD []\nis_a: GO:0042784 ! symbiont-mediated suppression of host complement activation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26389\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-11-22T15:34:16Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141117\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host complement activation by recruitment of complement control protein\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process by which a symbiont prevents the activation of host complement by binding a soluble complement control protein (CCP) of the host and recruiting it to the microbe surface. The normal role of CCPs is to prevent complement activation on 'self' cellular targets. When soluble CCPs are recuited to the surface of a microbe, the complement fails to activate.\" [PMID:17513779, PMID:22540535, PMID:24129254, PMID:27304426]\nsynonym: \"suppression of complement activation by another organism by recruitment of complement control protein\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"suppression of complement activation by another organism by recuitement of complement control protein\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0042784 ! symbiont-mediated suppression of host complement activation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26389\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-11-22T15:35:52Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141129\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host signal transduction pathway via antagonism of host cell surface receptor\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process by which a symbiont alters or subverts a host cell surface receptor-mediated signal transduction pathway by binding to and inhibiting the receptor of the pathway. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:10221874, PMID:22714643]\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated perturbation of host signal transduction pathway via antagonism of host cell surface receptor\" BROAD []\nis_a: GO:0052029 ! symbiont-mediated suppression of host signal transduction pathway\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26310\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-12-14T12:16:15Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141130\nname: symbiont-mediated inactivation of host ribosome\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts translation of mRNA into protein in its host by inactivating its ribosomes.\" [PMID:1324134]\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated host ribosome inactivation\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0039604 ! symbiont-mediated suppression of host translation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26184\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-12-14T12:22:56Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141135\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host chemokine signal transduction pathway\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont interferes with, inhibits or disrupts a chemokine signaling pathway, a G protein-coupled receptor signal transduction pathway activated by a chemokine. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:16581912]\nis_a: GO:0075120 ! symbiont-mediated suppression of host G protein-coupled receptor signal transduction\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0070098 ! chemokine-mediated signaling pathway\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26683\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-12-20T15:40:32Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141140\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host immunoglobulin-mediated immune response\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont interferes with, inhibits or disrupts the normal execution of the immunoglobulin-mediated immune response of the host organism. One common mechanism by which this happens is the direct inhibition of immunoglobulin activity, by direct binding or modification. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:18426869, PMID:22256861, PMID:24753590]\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated suppression of host immunoglobulin activity\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0052562 ! symbiont-mediated suppression of host immune response\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26740\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2024-01-16T09:55:22Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141145\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host neutrophil extracellular trap formation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the formation of neutrophil extracellular traps by the host cell. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:30038902, PMID:34108482]\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated perturbation of host neutrophil extracellular trap formation\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated suppression of host neutrophil extracellular traps formation\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0052031 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host defense response\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0140645 ! neutrophil extracellular trap formation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26811\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2024-01-24T06:32:59Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141154\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host-directed shutoff of host translation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the host shutoff of host translation, a host response that prevents mRNA in the cell to be translated, to prevent the symbiont from expressing its genes. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:20563710, PMID:21622569]\nis_a: GO:0044414 ! symbiont-mediated suppression of host defenses\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26918\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2024-01-31T14:53:32Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141155\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host translation elongation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the translation elongation of host mRNA into protein, for example by directly inhibiting elongation factors. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:10657208, PMID:18281405, PMID:18448518]\nis_a: GO:0039656 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host gene expression\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0006414 ! translational elongation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26918\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2024-01-31T15:24:57Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141157\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host exocytosis\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal execution of  host exocytosis. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:17185412]\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0006887 ! exocytosis\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26985\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2024-02-07T15:18:55Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141158\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host phagosome maturation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal maturation of host phagosomes. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:21501366, PMID:30181274, PMID:30733336, PMID:30937925]\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0090382 ! phagosome maturation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26987\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2024-02-07T16:39:43Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141159\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host phagosome acidification\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal acidification of host phagosomes. Mechanisms by which a symbiont prevents host phagosome acidification include the inhibitition of host V-ATPase, the proton pump that acidifies the phagosome, or disruption of the phagosome membrane by pore-forming toxin. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:20333253, PMID:22087003, PMID:33505976]\nis_a: GO:0052031 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host defense response\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0090383 ! phagosome acidification\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26987\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2024-02-07T16:39:57Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141173\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host pro-inflammatory cytokine signaling\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process by which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts pro-inflammatory cytokine signaling in the host organism, either by disruption of production, sequesteration, or destruction of at least one component of the signaling pathway. Pro-inflammatory cytokines include: IL-1, IL-12, IL-18, TNF, IFN-gamma, and GM-CSF. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:20008527, PMID:24508400, PMID:32117813]\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host pro-inflammatory cytokine production\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression by symbiont of host pro-inflammatory cytokine production\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression by symbiont of host pro-inflammatory cytokine secretion\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated degradation of host pro-inflammatory cytokine\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated sequestering of host pro-inflammatory cytokine\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated suppression of host pro-inflammatory cytokine production\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0075109 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host receptor-mediated signal transduction\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item 