 aggregation in other organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in regulation of platelet aggregation in other organism\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29375\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2011-10-27T02:36:43Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044477\nname: venom-mediated suppression of platelet aggregation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism inhibits or disrupts platelet aggregation in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:fj, PMID:28435120, PMID:37818211]\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of platelet aggregation in another organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of platelet aggregation in other organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation suppressing platelet aggregation\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated suppression of platelet agglutination\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated suppression of thrombocyte aggregation\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0044483 ! venom-mediated perturbation of hemostasis\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0070527 ! platelet aggregation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18979\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-01-19T02:36:44Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044478\nname: venom-mediated platelet aggregation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances platelet aggregation in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl]\nsynonym: \"envenomation promoting platelet aggregation\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in positive regulation of platelet aggregation in another organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in positive regulation of platelet aggregation in other organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated platelet agglutination\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0044469 ! venom-mediated blood coagulation\nis_a: GO:0044483 ! venom-mediated perturbation of hemostasis\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0070527 ! platelet aggregation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29851\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-01-19T02:39:45Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0061478\nname: response to platelet aggregation inhibitor\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a platelet aggregation inhibitor stimulus.\" [GOC:dph]\nintersection_of: GO:0050896 ! response to stimulus\nintersection_of: has_primary_input GOCHE:50427 ! substance with platelet aggregation inhibitor role\ncreated_by: dph\ncreation_date: 2012-11-07T09:09:37Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0070527\nname: platelet aggregation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The adhesion of one platelet to one or more other platelets via adhesion molecules.\" [GOC:BHF, GOC:vk]\nsynonym: \"blood platelet aggregation\" EXACT [CL:0000233]\nsynonym: \"thrombocyte aggregation\" RELATED [CL:0000233]\nintersection_of: GO:0034109 ! homotypic cell-cell adhesion\nintersection_of: has_participant CL:0000233 ! platelet\nrelationship: part_of GO:0030168 ! platelet activation\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0090330\nname: regulation of platelet aggregation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of platelet aggregation. Platelet aggregation is the adhesion of one platelet to one or more other platelets via adhesion molecules.\" [GOC:dph, GOC:tb]\nintersection_of: GO:0065007 ! biological regulation\nintersection_of: regulates GO:0070527 ! platelet aggregation\nrelationship: r