{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778433197463,"sessionID":"ses_1ed2e5abdffeV49GJQcR5nFb98","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_8XdtFWRemCOalSlzebxAjZAG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Created `GO:7770070` symbiont-mediated suppression of host platelet aggregation.\n+\n+The new term follows the existing symbiont-mediated host-process suppression pattern and cites PMID:15045140 for a Staphylococcus aureus secreted protein that inhibits platelet aggregation. Full ontology validation passed. Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n*** Add File: PR_COMMENTS.md\n+## Summary\n+\n+Added `GO:7770070` symbiont-mediated suppression of host platelet aggregation.\n+\n+## Rationale\n+\n+The issue requested a new term for symbiont-mediated suppression of platelet aggregation. Existing GO precedent supports representing this as a symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process with a `negatively_regulates_in_another_organism` relation to `GO:0070527` platelet aggregation. This parallels the active venom-specific term `GO:0044477` venom-mediated suppression of platelet aggregation, while avoiding obsolete general platelet aggregation-in-another-organism terms.\n+\n+PMID:15045140 was validated and used as definition provenance. It describes the Staphylococcus aureus extracellular fibrinogen-binding protein Efb as a potent inhibitor of platelet aggregation.\n+\n+## Ontology Changes\n+\n+New term:\n+\n+```obo\n+id: GO:7770070\n+name: symbiont-mediated suppression of host platelet aggregation\n+namespace: biological_process\n+def: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts platelet aggregation in its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:15045140]\n+intersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\n+intersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0070527 ! platelet aggregation\n+```\n+\n+Synonyms added:\n+\n+* `negative regulation by symbiont of host platelet aggregation`\n+* `suppression by symbiont of host platelet aggregation`\n+* `symbiont-mediated inhibition of host platelet aggregation`\n+\n+## Validation\n+\n+* Baseline `make travis_build`: passed before edits.\n+* Post-edit `make travis_build`: passed.\n+* `linkml-reference-validator validate text-file` for `RESEARCH.md`: passed.\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+* [x] PLAN: Issue context analyzed; requested new term was clear from title.\n+* [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Current ontology validated before edits.\n+* [x] RESEARCH: PMID:15045140 validated and summarized in `RESEARCH.md`.\n+* [x] TERM-SEARCH: Existing platelet aggregation, obsolete platelet aggregation-in-another-organism, venom-mediated, and symbiont-mediated suppression terms checked.\n+* [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: Existing symbiont-mediated suppression precedent documented in `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md`.\n+* [x] EDITS: New term created in `terms/GO_7770070.obo` and checked into `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` with `obo-checkin.pl`.\n+* [x] RELATIONSHIPS: Logical definition uses `GO:0044003` plus `negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0070527`.\n+* [x] METADATA: Term tracker, `created_by`, and `creation_date` included for the new term.\n+* [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: Full `make travis_build` passed after edits.\n+* [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: PMID support text validated with `linkml-reference-validator`.\n+* [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: Ontology change committed locally.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@\n+Created `GO:7770070` symbiont-mediated suppression of host platelet aggregation.\n+\n+The new term follows the existing symbiont-mediated host-process suppression pattern and cites PMID:15045140 for a Staphylococcus aureus secreted protein that inhibits platelet aggregation. Full ontology validation passed. Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,48 @@\n+## Summary\n+\n+Added `GO:7770070` symbiont-mediated suppression of host platelet aggregation.\n+\n+## Rationale\n+\n+The issue requested a new term for symbiont-mediated suppression of platelet aggregation. Existing GO precedent supports representing this as a symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process with a `negatively_regulates_in_another_organism` relation to `GO:0070527` platelet aggregation. This parallels the active venom-specific term `GO:0044477` venom-mediated suppression of platelet aggregation, while avoiding obsolete general platelet aggregation-in-another-organism terms.\n+\n+PMID:15045140 was validated and used as definition provenance. It describes the Staphylococcus aureus extracellular fibrinogen-binding protein Efb as a potent inhibitor of platelet aggregation.\n+\n+## Ontology Changes\n+\n+New term:\n+\n+```obo\n+id: GO:7770070\n+name: symbiont-mediated suppression of host platelet aggregation\n+namespace: biological_process\n+def: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts platelet aggregation in its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:15045140]\n+intersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\n+intersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0070527 ! platelet aggregation\n+```\n+\n+Synonyms added:\n+\n+* `negative regulation by symbiont of host platelet aggregation`\n+* `suppression by symbiont of host platelet aggregation`\n+* `symbiont-mediated inhibition of host platelet aggregation`\n+\n+## Validation\n+\n+* Baseline `make travis_build`: passed before edits.\n+* Post-edit `make travis_build`: passed.\n+* `linkml-reference-validator validate text-file` for `RESEARCH.md`: passed.\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+* [x] PLAN: Issue context analyzed; requested new term was clear from title.\n+* [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Current ontology validated before edits.\n+* [x] RESEARCH: PMID:15045140 validated and summarized in `RESEARCH.md`.\n+* [x] TERM-SEARCH: Existing platelet aggregation, obsolete platelet aggregation-in-another-organism, venom-mediated, and symbiont-mediated suppression terms checked.\n+* [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: Existing symbiont-mediated suppression precedent documented in `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md`.\n+* [x] EDITS: New term created in `terms/GO_7770070.obo` and checked into `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` with `obo-checkin.pl`.\n+* [x] RELATIONSHIPS: Logical definition uses `GO:0044003` plus `negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0070527`.\n+* [x] METADATA: Term tracker, `created_by`, and `creation_date` included for the new term.\n+* [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: Full `make travis_build` passed after edits.\n+* [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: PMID support text validated with `linkml-reference-validator`.\n+* [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: Ontology change committed locally.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@\n+Created `GO:7770070` symbiont-mediated suppression of host platelet aggregation.\n+\n+The new term follows the existing symbiont-mediated host-process suppression pattern and cites PMID:15045140 for a Staphylococcus aureus secreted protein that inhibits platelet aggregation. Full ontology validation passed. Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n","additions":3,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"PR_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,48 @@\n+## Summary\n+\n+Added `GO:7770070` symbiont-mediated suppression of host platelet aggregation.\n+\n+## Rationale\n+\n+The issue requested a new term for symbiont-mediated suppression of platelet aggregation. Existing GO precedent supports representing this as a symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process with a `negatively_regulates_in_another_organism` relation to `GO:0070527` platelet aggregation. This parallels the active venom-specific term `GO:0044477` venom-mediated suppression of platelet aggregation, while avoiding obsolete general platelet aggregation-in-another-organism terms.\n+\n+PMID:15045140 was validated and used as definition provenance. It describes the Staphylococcus aureus extracellular fibrinogen-binding protein Efb as a potent inhibitor of platelet aggregation.\n+\n+## Ontology Changes\n+\n+New term:\n+\n+```obo\n+id: GO:7770070\n+name: symbiont-mediated suppression of host platelet aggregation\n+namespace: biological_process\n+def: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts platelet aggregation in its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:15045140]\n+intersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\n+intersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0070527 ! platelet aggregation\n+```\n+\n+Synonyms added:\n+\n+* `negative regulation by symbiont of host platelet aggregation`\n+* `suppression by symbiont of host platelet aggregation`\n+* `symbiont-mediated inhibition of host platelet aggregation`\n+\n+## Validation\n+\n+* Baseline `make travis_build`: passed before edits.\n+* Post-edit `make travis_build`: passed.\n+* `linkml-reference-validator validate text-file` for `RESEARCH.md`: passed.\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+* [x] PLAN: Issue context analyzed; requested new term was clear from title.\n+* [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Current ontology validated before edits.\n+* [x] RESEARCH: PMID:15045140 validated and summarized in `RESEARCH.md`.\n+* [x] TERM-SEARCH: Existing platelet aggregation, obsolete platelet aggregation-in-another-organism, venom-mediated, and symbiont-mediated suppression terms checked.\n+* [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: Existing symbiont-mediated suppression precedent documented in `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md`.\n+* [x] EDITS: New term created in `terms/GO_7770070.obo` and checked into `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` with `obo-checkin.pl`.\n+* [x] RELATIONSHIPS: Logical definition uses `GO:0044003` plus `negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0070527`.\n+* [x] METADATA: Term tracker, `created_by`, and `creation_date` included for the new term.\n+* [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: Full `make travis_build` passed after edits.\n+* [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: PMID support text validated with `linkml-reference-validator`.\n+* [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: Ontology change committed locally.\n","additions":48,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778433197455,"end":1778433197460}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_036883a70c6b0bdb016a00bca0e384819488df182cba041c8c"}},"id":"prt_e12e0d499001NmRYseYciZebEE","sessionID":"ses_1ed2e5abdffeV49GJQcR5nFb98","messageID":"msg_e12e0cc3f001SXRsOj5Lghm89w"}}
